BEGIN_TEXT
Supermassive black holes are thought to exist at the centre of many galaxies. 
$BR
a) What is the radius of such an object if it has a mass of \(10^{9}\) Suns?

$BR
$BR

\{ans_rule(40)\} m

$BR
$BR
END_TEXT

